2
00:01:20,313 --> 00:01:25,808
雪菲德营区 夏威夷，1941年

3
00:01:37,597 --> 00:01:39,155
马吉欧，你好
Hey, Maggio! Hello!

4
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:42,097
你好，普威特
Hiya, Prew.

5
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:49,432
 你怎么会来这里？  我从薛福特堡被调过来
  What are you doing here?   Transferred from Fort Shafter.

6
00:01:50,510 --> 00:01:52,273
你离开号角兵团了吗？
You quit the Bugle Corps?

7
00:01:52,479 --> 00:01:55,471
 为了来这里？  不是我自己选的
  For here?   I didn't pick it.

8
00:01:55,682 --> 00:02:00,551
你错了！他们可以把这个军团 还给卡斯特将军
You made a mistake. This outfit they can give back to General Custer.

9
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:08,359
上尉还没进办公室
Captain ain't in yet.

10
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:12,321
我四处去看看
I'll look around.

11
00:02:29,549 --> 00:02:32,177
你以为你在干什么？
What do you think you're doing?

12
00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:36,482
 你叫什么名字？  普威特，从薛福特堡调来
  What's your name?   Prewitt. Transfer from Fort Shafter.

13
00:02:37,790 --> 00:02:42,318
 我听说过你  我也听说过你，上士
  I heard about you.   I heard about you too, sergeant.

14
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:47,091
这里是步兵团 你在太阳下山前不该玩乐的
This is a rifle outfit. You ain't supposed to have fun before sundown.

15
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:49,825
把球杆收起来，跟我来
Put up your cue and come along.

16
00:02:59,245 --> 00:03:02,408
葛兰昨天去过医院 你的报告写好了吗？
Grand went to the hospital yesterday. Did you do the report?

17
00:03:02,582 --> 00:03:04,948
 我还没有时间写，上士  你是文书官
  No time, sergeant.   You're the company clerk.

18
00:03:05,151 --> 00:03:09,315
医官很晚才将病历送来 我会写的
The medics didn't bring back the sick book till late. I'll do it.

19
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:12,549
多谢！我已经替你写好了
Thanks, I already done it for you.

20
00:03:16,963 --> 00:03:21,730
你是薛福特堡最棒的号手 也是全岛最棒的
You're the best bugler at Shafter. On this whole island.

21
00:03:21,935 --> 00:03:23,425
那倒是事实
That's true.

22
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:30,536
我同情你，但站在我的立场 我还是不了解你
I feel for you, pal. But from my position, I can't quite reach you.

23
00:03:36,649 --> 00:03:38,310
立正！
Hut!

24
00:03:40,653 --> 00:03:41,779
 稍息  早安，长官
  At ease.   Morning, sir.

25
00:03:41,988 --> 00:03:45,788
有什么特别的事吗？ 我只有几分钟时间
Have anything special for me? I only have a few minutes.

26
00:03:45,992 --> 00:03:49,860
 是的，长官，有新兵报到  是的，进来
  Yes, sir. New man here.   Oh, yes. Come in.

27
00:03:56,836 --> 00:04:00,101
长官，罗勃普威特大兵 向连长报到
Sir, Private Robert E. Lee Prewitt, reporting to the company commander.

28
00:04:00,306 --> 00:04:03,503
稍息！服役纪录呢？
At ease. Where's that service record?

29
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:11,574
生于肯塔基州 在维州梅尔堡入伍，第一号手
Born in Kentucky, enlisted first at Fort Meyer, Virginia. First bugler.

30
00:04:12,218 --> 00:04:15,346
我通常会跟新报到的人谈谈
I make it a policy to talk to my new men.

31
00:04:15,555 --> 00:04:17,682
本军团的运作很顺利
I have a smooth running outfit.

32
00:04:17,857 --> 00:04:22,191
如果我欣赏某位士兵 他便能迅速升任无委任状士官
If I like a soldier, he can get to be a non commissioned officer quick.

33
00:04:22,595 --> 00:04:25,962
但他得让我看看他够精明
But he has to show me he's got it on the ball.

34
00:04:26,165 --> 00:04:28,156
你在号角兵团惹了什么麻烦？
What was your trouble in the Bugle Corps?

35
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:31,132
 没有惹麻烦，长官  那么你为何请调？
  No trouble, sir.   Why did you transfer?

36
00:04:31,304 --> 00:04:34,273
那是个人因素
It was a personal matter.

37
00:04:34,474 --> 00:04:37,500
 你有什么想问的吗？上士  是的，长官
  Something you want to ask, sergeant?   Yes, sir.

38
00:04:37,710 --> 00:04:39,473
普威特，你原是下士
Prewitt, you was a corporal.

39
00:04:39,679 --> 00:04:44,412
你却自动降为大兵 调至步兵团，为什么？
You took a bust to buck private to transfer to an infantry outfit. Why?

40
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:48,178
是因为你喜欢步行 还是你受不了吹号角？
Because you like to hike, or because you couldn't stand to bugle?

41
00:04:48,354 --> 00:04:50,288
完全是个人因素
It was a personal matter.

42
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:53,983
 这由连长决定  是怎么样？
  Company commander decides that.   Well?

43
00:04:55,628 --> 00:05:00,691
我担任了两年的第一号手 但军士长的朋友调了进来
I was first bugler for two years. The topkick's friend transferred in.

44
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:03,562
第二天他便成了第一号手
The next day he was made first bugler.

45
00:05:03,736 --> 00:05:08,070
 我吹号的技巧比他好  你因此而离开？
  I was a better bugler.   You left because of that?

46
00:05:09,008 --> 00:05:13,001
 或许是有些不太理智  他的情感受到伤害
  Maybe it ain't sensible.   His feelings were hurt.

47
00:05:13,212 --> 00:05:14,679
他们现在给我们的人手是这样的
The kids they send us now!

48
00:05:14,881 --> 00:05:18,248
我们会恢复你的官阶 或许还让你升官
We'll get your stripes back, maybe an extra one.

49
00:05:18,451 --> 00:05:20,851
 你知道你为何在参谋本部？  不知道，长官
  You know why you're in G Company?   No, sir.

50
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:24,979
我利用了一些关系 我现在是军团的拳击教练
I pulled a few strings. I'm the regimental boxing coach.

51
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:26,147
是的，长官
Yes, sir.

52
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:30,989
两年前，你就应该打赢康纳斯的
You should have won your fight with Conners 2 years ago.

53
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:31,960
谢谢你，长官
Thank you, sir.

54
00:05:32,332 --> 00:05:36,530
去年我们在决赛时败北 但今年我一定要获胜
We lost the finals last year, but I mean to win this year.

55
00:05:36,736 --> 00:05:38,601
我需要中量级的好手
I need a top middleweight.

56
00:05:40,306 --> 00:05:44,709
 很抱歉，长官！我已不打拳了  不打拳？为什么？
  I'm sorry, sir. I quit fighting.   Quit fighting? What for?

57
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:51,039
一年多前，或许你听说过 迪西威尔斯的事
Over a year ago. Maybe you heard about what happened with Dixie Wells?

58
00:05:51,217 --> 00:05:54,550
 你是指受伤的那家伙？  是的，长官
  You mean that fellow that got hurt?   Yes, sir.

59
00:05:54,754 --> 00:05:58,315
我是听说过 我能了解你的感受
I heard about that. I can understand how you feel.

60
00:05:58,524 --> 00:06:01,516
 那种事难免会发生  他是我不打的原因，长官
  Those things happen.   That's why I quit, sir.

61
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:05,095
你不能因为死了一个人 就说“停战”
You can't say "stop war" because one man died.

62
00:06:05,298 --> 00:06:09,860
我们的拳击课程 是最能提振士气的
Our fighting program is the best morale builder we have.

63
00:06:16,442 --> 00:06:19,172
军团已经有一位走音的号手
I've got a mighty sour company bugler.

64
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:22,780
 你喜欢这工作吗？  如果要打拳就不喜欢
  How'd you like the job?   Not if it means fighting.

65
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:26,749
你打算取得独行侠的声誉吗？
You trying to acquire a reputation as a lone wolf?

66
00:06:26,919 --> 00:06:30,912
军队里不能有个人主义存在
In the Army, it's not the individual that counts.

67
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:35,186
军团不会对你施加压力
We won't put pressure on you in my outfit.

68
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:39,058
你只要不犯错就行了
Just don't make any mistakes, that's all.

69
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,257
我要进城去，还有事吗？
I'm going into town. Anything else?

70
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:44,301
 军团的预算报告要交了  你写吧
  The company fund report is due.   You do it.

71
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:45,994
 没有其他了？  不是的，长官
  Is that all?   No, sir.

72
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:50,938
由你全权处理 下午如果有事，代签我的名字
You fix it up. If there's anything this afternoon, sign my name.

73
00:06:51,144 --> 00:06:53,374
 我不会回来了  是的，长官
  I won't be back.   Yes, sir.

74
00:06:55,715 --> 00:07:01,085
如果不是我在后面替他打理 他早就完蛋了
He'd strangle in his own spit without me to swab his throat.

75
00:07:01,287 --> 00:07:02,720
走吧！
Come on.

76
00:07:13,699 --> 00:07:17,635
你已从军五年？五年半？
You been in the Army five years? Five and a half?

77
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:21,830
你不认为是时候 该学聪明些了吗？
Don't you think it's about time you got smart?

78
00:07:22,575 --> 00:07:26,978
你拒绝了炸药荷姆斯 等于是自找死路
By turning down Dynamite Holmes, you put your head in a noose.

79
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:31,207
当拳击手很轻松 你最好学学怎么当兵
Things are soft for a boxer. You'd better know how to soldier.

80
00:07:31,417 --> 00:07:34,443
我当得和任何人一样好
I can soldier with any man.

81
00:07:46,265 --> 00:07:49,701
这里快变成夏威夷皇家饭店了
This is getting to be like the Royal Hawaiian Hotel.

82
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:57,876
 她是谁？  她是荷姆斯上尉夫人
  Who is that?   She's Captain Holmes' wife.

83
00:07:58,077 --> 00:08:02,241
你会被逼赛拳，因为荷姆斯上尉 想成为荷姆斯少校
You'll fight, because Captain Holmes wants to be Major Holmes.

84
00:08:02,448 --> 00:08:05,349
他认为赢得拳赛就能升官
He thinks he'll make it with a winning team.

85
00:08:05,551 --> 00:08:09,817
就算不为他，也为了我 我的工作就是让他高兴
If not for him, for me. My job is to keep him happy.

86
00:08:10,022 --> 00:08:12,013
他愈高兴，就愈不会来烦我
The happier he is, the less he bothers me...

87
00:08:12,225 --> 00:08:14,819
而且我就会把他的军团 管理得更好
...and the better I run his company.

88
00:08:15,795 --> 00:08:20,095
 我们清楚我们的立场吧？  我知道自己的立场
  We know where we stand, don't we?   I know where I stand.

89
00:08:20,299 --> 00:08:25,760
 不依他的人将一事无成  在拓荒时期或许还可以
  A man don't go his way, he's nothing.   In the pioneer days, he could.

90
00:08:25,972 --> 00:08:28,770
但是现在你必须照章行事
But today you got to play ball.

91
00:08:34,547 --> 00:08:38,711
列瓦！我能不能走进来之后 看到你用双手在工作呢？
Leva! Can't I walk up and find you working with both hands?!

92
00:08:38,885 --> 00:08:43,254
 你们付我的薪水根本不够  替这个人准备些用品
  Not on what you people pay me.   Draw this man some supplies.

93
00:08:43,422 --> 00:08:46,721
寝室在顶楼 把你的袋子放好后再回来
Squad room is on the top floor. Leave your bags and come back.

94
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:51,659
列瓦会帮你 可以替你省下四，五趟路
Leva'll help you. Save you four or five trips.

95
00:08:51,898 --> 00:08:52,887
谢谢
Thanks.

96
00:08:53,065 --> 00:08:57,001
我不喜欢浪费体力 你会需要你的体力的
I hate to see energy wasted. You'll be needing yours.

97
00:09:00,006 --> 00:09:05,808
 他看来是个好人  我了解他这种人！他是死脑筋
  Looks like a good man.   I know his type. He's a hard head.

98
00:09:15,855 --> 00:09:20,758
 大热天她还穿毛衣  我想她一定冷若冰霜
  Her and them sweaters.   I bet she's colder than an iceberg.

99
00:09:20,927 --> 00:09:24,158
不会的，军士长，她很懂世故的
Not her, Top. She knows the score.

100
00:09:24,363 --> 00:09:25,887
是吗？
Is that right?

101
00:09:26,098 --> 00:09:32,094
 我在布里斯堡听说很多事  是吗？
  At Fort Bliss, I heard plenty.   You did, huh?

102
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:37,004
我认识她的伴侣 你不用告诉我了
I know the guys she played around with. So don't tell me.

103
00:09:37,176 --> 00:09:40,111
我没有！是你在告诉我！
I ain't. You're telling me.

104
00:09:45,251 --> 00:09:47,378
 早安，上士  早安，夫人
  Good morning, sergeant.   Morning, ma'am.

105
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:51,580
 我来找我丈夫  他到城里公干去了
  I'm looking for my husband.   He's in town on business.

106
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:55,022
他说有东西留给我 你知道吗？
He was to leave some things. Do you know about them?

107
00:09:55,194 --> 00:10:00,427
 不知道，夫人！我能效劳吗？  不用了，谢谢
  No, ma'am. Anything I can do?   No, thanks.

108
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:03,466
我很乐意效劳的，夫人
I'd be glad to help, ma'am.

109
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:15,711
我丈夫告诉我很多你的事，上士
My husband's told me a lot about you, sergeant.

110
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:19,180
 他说你做事的效率很高  是的，夫人
  He says you're very efficient.   Yes, ma'am.

111
00:10:19,885 --> 00:10:25,255
 你为何如此有效率？上士  因为我天生聪颖，夫人
  What makes you efficient, sergeant?   I was born smart, ma'am.

112
00:10:25,992 --> 00:10:30,190
我喜欢这个说法 再见了，上士
I love that. Well, goodbye, sergeant.

113
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:37,094
 她可真是啊，对吧？  真是什么？
  Man, she sure is one, ain't she?   One what?

114
00:10:37,303 --> 00:10:40,295
 真是尤物  我看过更美的
  One woman.   I've seen better.

115
00:10:47,747 --> 00:10:48,975
凯伦
Karen!

116
00:10:49,181 --> 00:10:50,478
凯伦
Karen!

117
00:11:01,527 --> 00:11:04,087
 对不起！我回来晚了  没有关系
  Sorry I'm late.   It doesn't matter.

118
00:11:04,263 --> 00:11:07,699
我在军官乐部 被史莱特将军缠住了
I got tied up with General Slater at the Officer's Club.

119
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:10,664
将军说了些什么？
What did the general have to say?

120
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:15,830
他说要成功！战时要成功 和平时更要成功
Success, he said. Success in war, success in peacetime.

121
00:11:16,042 --> 00:11:18,602
对我的升官却一句也没提
And not a word about my promotion.

122
00:11:18,811 --> 00:11:21,746
有时我觉得他想降我职
Sometimes I think he's waiting to ship me down.

123
00:11:21,947 --> 00:11:26,281
少去奉承将军们 多跟你的军团在一起
Spend less time buttering generals and more time with your company.

124
00:11:26,485 --> 00:11:29,249
军团可以照顾自己
The company takes care of itself.

125
00:11:29,588 --> 00:11:36,118
 我今天去找过你  我到卡纳欧黑办事
  I looked for you, today.   I had some business at Kaneohe.

126
00:11:36,295 --> 00:11:40,129
 你不介意吧？  当然
  That was all right, wasn't it?   Of course.

127
00:11:40,332 --> 00:11:43,392
我没有权利过问 那是我们同意的
I have no right to inquire. That was our agreement.

128
00:11:43,602 --> 00:11:45,126
为什么要提起这件事？
Why bring it up?

129
00:11:45,337 --> 00:11:48,966
我可不是你 认为的那种笨女人
I'm not as stupid as you think all women are.

130
00:11:49,175 --> 00:11:50,870
这话什么意思？
Now, what does that mean?

131
00:11:51,077 --> 00:11:53,443
 你又在指控什么了？  没事
  What's the accusation now?   Nothing.

132
00:11:53,646 --> 00:11:57,343
你跟多少女人出去 也不干我的事，对吧？
It's none of my business how many women you go out with, is it?

133
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,814
但我希望你能诚实
But I wish you were honest.

134
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:05,389
为什么要隐瞒？ 我们之间已经这样了
Why hide anything? The way things are between us now?

135
00:12:05,591 --> 00:12:09,027
你凭什么一直这样指控我？
What right have you to always accuse me?

136
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:10,557
凭什么？
What right?

137
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:18,765
你还要再翻旧帐吗？ 我还得忍受多久？
Are you going back to that again? How long before I live that down?

138
00:12:19,805 --> 00:12:22,865
我得跟你说几次那是意外？
How many times do I tell you it was an accident?

139
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:24,406
拜托你，唐纳
Please, Dana.

140
00:12:26,145 --> 00:12:29,945
我要睡了！请离开我的卧房
I'm going to bed. Please get out of my bedroom.

141
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:01,204
荷姆斯上尉说你不想打拳
Captain Holmes says you don't want to fight.

142
00:13:01,413 --> 00:13:06,112
 没错  我请你喝杯啤酒而且谈一谈
  That's right.   Let's buy you a beer and talk.

143
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:11,780
 我们是军团的拳击手  我猜也是
  We're the company boxers.   I figured.

144
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:26,401
我真希望他在我家乡的弹子房
What I would give to have him in the pool room in my home town!

145
00:13:29,441 --> 00:13:32,205
如果你跟以前一样打得好 我们就赢定了
If you box as good as before, we'll be a cinch.

146
00:13:32,411 --> 00:13:36,780
别忘了！区冠军还可以 放十天的假
Don't forget: Division champs get ten day furloughs, son.

147
00:13:40,886 --> 00:13:44,378
我是艾克葛罗维奇 是你的排长
I'm lke Galovitch. Platoon guide of your platoon.

148
00:13:44,590 --> 00:13:46,717
别以为你很强悍，普威特
Don't think you're tough, Prewitt.

149
00:13:46,926 --> 00:13:50,327
现在不说话 到野外可就要喊救命了
You no talk now, but in the field you sing different.

150
00:13:50,529 --> 00:13:53,726
如果他不想打拳 就用不打
He don't have to fight if he don't want to.

